### Plan Overview

**24 tasks** across **7 milestones**, ~10 nights on the critical path:

| Milestone | Name | Nights | Critical Path |
|-----------|------|--------|--------------|
| M1 | Infrastructure Foundation | 1 | Yes |
| M2 | Megamap Layout & Lumber Zone Assets | 1 | Yes |
| M3 | Lumber Production Chain | 2 | Yes |
| M4 | Team Wallets, Sell Depot & Round Manager | 2 | Yes |
| M5 | Upgrade System | 2 | Yes |
| M6 | DataStore Persistence & Real-Time Leaderboard | 1 | Yes |
| M7 | Monetisation Layer | 1 | No |

### Key architectural decisions made:
1. **ConveyorBelt is server-side physical parts** (not client tweens) — required for post-launch steal mechanic
2. **Upgrade state is round-scoped** (resets each round) — preserves competitive balance
3. **CashPad → personal wallet; Sell Depot → team wallet** — resolves spec ambiguity about dual income flows
4. **Win bonus drop = cosmetic ticket** stored in DataStore (cosmetics store is post-launch)
5. **Boost Bucks ratio** is a tunable constant with placeholder value — OQ flagged for human review before launch

### Out-of-scope items correctly excluded:
Mining, Oil, Sabotage, Steal, Anti-Sabotage Defenses, Cosmetics Store, cross-server features, VIP servers
